12q14 microdeletion syndrome can be inherited in families in an autosomal dominant pattern. This means that a parent who has this deletion has a 50-50 or 1 in 2 chance of passing it on to each of his or her children. <br />
<br />
In some cases, this deletion occurs for the first time in a person (de novo), and is not inherited from a parent.[15098][15099][15101]&nbsp;
